textline.data: The controller shall interface with optical sensors
on the rover to compute a machine learning vision
The controller shall not command the rover to
exceed a speed of 152 meters per hour
The controller shall use a robotic
arm hidden under the rover that
stores chalk-sized samples
The controller shall use a robotic
arm measuring 2.1 meters to
elaborate rock coring and store
geologic samples in small tubes
The controller shall interface with
7 scientific cameras: 2 MASTCAM-Z,
1 Supercam, 2 SHERLOC, 1 PIXL, 1 MEDA
The controller shall interface
with 3 landing cameras
The controller shall interface with 9
engineering cameras: 2 NAVCAM,
6 HAZCAM, 1 CAGECAM
The controller shall interface with multiple cameras
The controller shall save audio recordings from
the 2 microphones
The controller shall interface with the
MOXIE module
The controller shall use information from a ground navigation
system on the rover to find its own way across the martian terrain
The controller shall be able to self drive the rover
for at least 200 meters per day
The controller shall operate the rover for a minimum of 1
martian year.
When a drill order is received, the controller shall
order the drill to take a samples of the soil and store
them in a small tube under the rover
The controller shall operate the rover's instruments and sensors in order to
investigate bio signatures on Mars to investigate whether or not life exist on the
The controller shall interface with
the RIMFAX module
